<!doctype html>
<!--[if IE 7 ]>    <html lang="<%= @lang %>" class="no-js ie7"> <![endif]-->
<!--[if IE 8 ]>    <html lang="<%= @lang %>" class="no-js ie8"> <![endif]-->
<!--[if IE 9 ]>    <html lang="<%= @lang %>" class="no-js ie9"> <![endif]-->
<!--[if (gt IE 9)|!(IE)]><!--> <html lang="<%= @lang %>" class="no-js"> <!--<![endif]-->

<head>
    <title>Railsgun - <%= yield :title %></title>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="description" content="Railsgun" />
    <meta name="keywords" content= "railsgun" /> 
    <meta name="authors" content= "Matteo Papadopoulos, Silvio Relli" />

    <link rel="shortcut icon" href="/favicon.ico" />

    <!-- some mobiles configurations -->
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    
    <!-- 57px icon for iphone/ipad -->
    <link rel="apple-touch-icon" href="" />
    <meta name="apple-mobile-web-app-status-bar-style" content="black-translucent" />
    <meta name="format-detection" content="telephone=yes" />
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge,chrome=1">

    <%# you can remove these two lines to load jquery from your local path %>
    <script type="text/javascript" src="https://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/1.5.1/jquery.min.js"></script>
    <script type="text/javascript" src="https://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jqueryui/1.8.9/jquery-ui.min.js"></script>
    
    <%= javascript_include_tag  "rails",
                                "modernizr",
                                "jquery.equalHeightColumns.min",
                                "application"
    %>
    <%= csrf_meta_tag %>
    
    
    <!-- STYLESHEETS -->
    <%= stylesheet_link_tag "hive", "style", "demo" %>
    
    <%= yield :extra_head %>
</head>

<body>
    <div class="hive_12">
        <div class="cell_12">
            <header>
                <hgroup>
                    <h1>Rails Gun</h1>
                    <h2>How to shoot a fly with a cannon</h2>
                </hgroup>
                <nav>
                    <ul>
                        <li><a href="https://github.com/cantierecreativo/railsgun"  target="_blank">Fork on GitHub</a></li>
                        <li><a href="http://twitter.com/#!/teamcantiere" target="_blank">@the author</a></li>
                        <li><a href="http://www.cantierecreativo.net"  target="_blank">Cantiere Creativo</a></li>
                    </ul>
                </nav>
            </header>
        </div>
    
        <div class="cell_8" id="container">
            <article>
                <p>Your content will be shown here.</p>
                <%= yield %>
                
                <h1>The layout</h1>
                <p>This is just a simple layout we provide to begin a new project. There is an empty file named "application.html.erb.clean" that has this structure withou content. You should forst delete this original "application.html.erb" fil and the rename the "application.html.erb.clean" in "application.html.erb"</p>
                
                <h1>RailsGun use cell</h1>
                <p>Here, on the right, there is an example to use a cell to generate e two levels menu <pre>render_cell :menu, :two_levels, :page => @page</pre></p>
                
                <h1>The spleen_scss library</h1>
                <p>RailsGun use the <a href="https://github.com/spleenteo/spleen_scss" target="_blank">spleen_scss</a> library. To use it you should:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Remove the demo css from the head of this layout <pre>stylesheet_link_tag "hive", "style", "demo"</pre></li>
                    <li>Open a terminal and launch this command from the root of your railsgun project dir:
                        <pre>sass -C -t compact --watch app/stylesheets/:public/stylesheets/</pre>
                    </li>
                    <li>Now you can modify the "app/stylesheets/style.scss" to design your template as you prefer.</li>
                </ul>
                
                <h2>The mixin(s)</h2>
                <p>With spleen scss library you also have some mixin scss function availables as little shortcuts to css3 funcionality as:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Box Shadow: @include shadow(2px, 2px, #000)</li>
                    <li>Rounded corners @include rounded(7px)</li>
                    <li>Web Fonts (to be configured)</li>
                </ul>
                
            </article>
        </div>
        <div class="cell_4">
            <aside>
                <header>
                    <h1>Pages</h1>
                </header>
                <%= render_cell :menu, :two_levels, :page => @page %>
                
                <%# use your site with remote js loading %>
                <%#= render_cell :menu, :two_levels, :page => @page, :remote => true %>
            </aside>
        </div>

        <div class="cell_12">
            <footer>
                <div class="cell_4 alpha">
                    <section>
                        footer 1
                    </section>
                </div>
                <div class="cell_4">
                    <section>
                        footer 2
                    </section>
                </div>
                <div class="cell_4 omega">
                    <section>
                        footer 3
                    </section>
                </div>
            </footer>
        </div>

    </div>
</body>